{
  "texts": [
    "These adaptations and tweaks may happen either when existing rules are applied by courts or authorities in specific cases or in a preventative way by lawmakers amending existing laws.",
    "A parallel could be drawn in this respect with how tax and labour laws have been applied to platforms allowing peer-to-peer economic exchanges, such as Airbnb and Uber.",
    "In matters of taxation, it was unclear whether existing laws would apply to peer-to-peer, short-term rentals made through Airbnb, especially concerning tourist taxes that, in major cities around the world, local administrations impose on tourists and that are usually collected by hotels and operators of other traditional forms of touristic accommodation rentals.",
    "Such taxes, along with many other aspects of the economic activity allowed by Airbnb, have been regulated in major tourist cities after such cities experienced the negative consequences of the rise in such types of rentals for tourists, 70 in particular with respect to the payment by hosts of tourism taxes.",
    "71 To achieve this shift in tax rules, 65 S McCallum, \"ChatGPT Banned in Italy over Privacy Concerns\" (BBC News, 31 March 2023) <https://www.bbc."
  ]
}